description:
Taken in Ampara, Sri Lanka, the photograph on the cover of this gallery exposes a distressing reality: due to the reduction of natural habitats and the absence of efficient waste management, elephants are attracted to eat garbage dangerously close to human habitation.

Plastic waste threatens their lives, yet currently thereâ€™s no effective solution. Waste accumulation near forests lures elephants, and many other animals, away from their natural habitats, jeopardising their safety.

During photographer Damith Osuranga Danthanarayana â€˜s exploration, a small elephant was found, hurt by a homemade explosive.

This image and all the others in this carousel feature in this yearâ€™s Earth Photo awards, which showcase the issues affecting the climate and life on our planet. Swipe through to see and read more.

